<P>&nbsp&nbsp EverTools is a collection of 3rd party utilities for use with
Verant Interactive's online mass-multiplayer game EverQuest.  EverTools
contains an entire set of various tools.  Some of these tools are listed
below :</p>

 <ul>
 <li><a href="#everchat">EverChat - Realtime Chatting</a>
 <li>EverLaunch - Game launcher and profile editor
 <li>EverLogs - Log File Parser
 <li>EverMon 3.0 - Server Monitor
 <li>EverNews - News Updater and Alerter
 </ul><br>

<a name="everchat"></a>
<B><U><FONT SIZE=+1>About EverChat</FONT></U></B><BR>

<P>&nbsp&nbsp EverChat is a means by which users can chat with each other
in real-time.  EverChat is a cross between IRC (Internet Relay Chat) and
the chatting you are familiar with on the EverQuest chat server.  Here
are some of the features and abilities of EverChat : </P>

 <ul>
 <li>Simple Interface - less commands to remember than IRC chatting
 <li>EverMon Scroll Bar updating - while chatting, EverChat can pass on real-time update messages to be shown on EverMon's scroll bar (assuming EverMon is open)
 <li>Multiple Channels - Unlike the chat in EverMon 2.1, you now have different channels you can select from
 <li>Public and Private Messages - ability not only to send to channels, but also privatly to other users as well
 </ul><br>

You can access the Online <a href=et_helptool.htm>EverTools Help File</a> for more information.

